sources.description:
Pinocchio - The most famous Italian fairy tale in the world for its enthralling metaphor of the relationship between father and son. The Collodian tradition, where a marionette becomes a child and learns to become a son, is combined with a modern, ironic, but profound, story of a father that learns to do the same.
